<h1>National and Community Service</h1>
<a href="http://ncccblog.americorps.gov/"><img src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-RhWHbAMc4dA/U8mCXL2xWXI/AAAAAAAABbY/yNP4KEIAKQI/s1600/Advisory+Board+Meeting.jpg" /></a>
<p>There are several ways to get involved with national and/or community service. One of the more fulfulling ways is to join an AmeriCorps program.</p>
<p>There are three distinct AmeriCorps programs: VISTA (Volunteers in Service to America), State and National, and the <a href="http://www.nationalservice.gov/programs/americorps/americorps-nccc">National Civilian Community Corps (NCCC)</a>.</p>
<p>NCCC is the only team-based traveling corps in the three programs. There are five NCCC campuses throughout the United States, representing the regions in which they are located.</p>

